Program: Outlook
Title: 16/08/2011
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p00jf3zk
Last Broadcast Date: Wed 17 Aug 2011
Extraordinary personal stories from around the world. Today, we speak to Jaran Berg, who got away as Anders Behring Breivik shot dead 69 people in Norway, and also to his father Ulf, who drove desperately towards the tragedy, not sure if his son was alive or dead. Also, our series on border guards continues on board a Finnish coastguard vessel patrolling the waters between Finland and Russia. Show less